The Windows version is a PE executable and uses KERNEL32.dll.
In 'make.scm' define WINDOWS #t to make this version.
'dream.exe' expects bootstrap.scm to exist in the 'C:/dream/' directory.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Make with 'dream make.scm'.
Test with 'dream r4rstest.scm'.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Additional non-standard procedures include:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
(get-module-handle STRING)                     ==> INTEGER ;;GetModuleHandleA
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
